  "orchestration_decision": "delegate",
  "decision_notes": "The problem is decomposed into checking the existence of k(n)=1 (power of 2) and then checking for k(n)=2 and k(n)=3 via modular arithmetic and properties of powers of 2 modulo 2023.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "helper_1",
      "instructions": "Determine if there exists an integer n such that 2023*n is a power of 2. Use the prime factorization of 2023 to justify your answer. This determines if the minimum k(n) can be 1."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_2",
      "instructions": "Determine if k(n)=2 is possible by checking if 2023 divides 2^a + 2^b for some integers a, b. Specifically, check if 2023 divides 2^m + 1 for some m. If k(n)=2 is impossible, investigate if k(n)=3 is possible by checking if 2023 divides 2^a + 2^b + 2^c for some integers a, b, c."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "The parent agent will take the result from helper_1 (whether k(n)=1 is possible) and the result from helper_2 (the smallest k(n) > 1). The minimum of these values is the final answer."
}
```

